# Librarian Job Manual

This file is loaded on every recall and handed to your LLM as part of the
system prompt. Treat it as the always-on rulebook for how the librarian
should compile answers.

## Core Functions

### RECALL (primary)

Accept `{"message": "...", "topic": "..."}`, search the vault, compile
relevant notes, return a citeable answer.

- Input: `POST /recall`
- Output: `{"result": "...", "topic": "...", "sources": [...]}`

### QUERY (simplified)

`GET /query?q=<topic>` — same as recall but treats the query as both message
and topic.

### STATUS

`GET /status` — health and configuration snapshot.

## Search Priority

When multiple files match, rank by keyword frequency. Daily logs and topic
files typically surface first because they tend to be the densest on recent
activity.

## Skip Filter

Don't bother searching for:
- Single-word acknowledgments ("ok", "cool", "hi", "yes", "no")
- Bare URLs
- Slash commands
- Empty or very short messages (< 10 chars)

## Citation Format

Cite sources inline as `[1]`, `[2]`, etc., matching the order they appear in
the sources list. Never invent a citation — if the notes don't back an answer,
say so.

## Identity Cache

The librarian reads `SOUL.md` on every recall but caches the contents in-memory
by mtime, so edits are picked up automatically without a restart.
